recap news coverage July 16:


AP:

https://www.newspapers.com/image/315175/?terms=Cowchilla

massive search, "life ceased its normal routine" in Chowchilla, 24 hours later no indication why they were kidnapped

Sheriff Bates said two sets of tracks on the bus tracks, suggesting an abudction "would have to be planned"

issued lookout for up to three vans travelling west

parents started calling late afternoon, some went to police station some went on search

FBI director director Kelly ordered Assistant FBI Director Gebhardt of LA office to "take personal charge" of the investigation


UPI:

https://www.newspapers.com/image/2387706/?terms=Chowchilla

open: fear mass kidnaping by radicals

first few paragraphs makes it sound like abducted before bus abandoned

more quotes saying "believe it was terrorists"

FBI and police "reluctant to label the disappearance an outright kidnapping"

nearly every van being stopped on main roads as result of police lookout issued

"There was no explanation of why the vans were being sought"

"dust patterns on the bus seats led authorities to believe the vehicle was empty at the time it was abandoned"

tracks from maybe two vechiles found beside bus tracks, maybe from hunters, heavy rain hampered investigation

checking out reports of van nearby, searched for van for a while but turned out to belong to fed dental program

"no legal basis" to call kidnapping and FBI agents not officially assigned to the case





conflicting:


