	...[Mike] He said he no longer has the bad dreams but he said that when he thinks back to July, 1976, "it's scary. I mena, I remember how scared I was. When Ed Ray told me that we were going to die if we stayed down there, kick the bucket, that right there is what made me want to dig out. I figured if I was going to die down there, then I might as well die trying to dig out. Because he (Ray) was an adult, I thought he knew what he was talking about.

	...Mike said he sometimes looks back on the time in the buried truck-trailer and he marvels at what he and Robert Gonzales accomplished. "I don't think I could do it right now--if I didn't think I was going to die. It's like the story you hear of the kid lifting the car off his dad. It got his adrenalin flowing. It was kind of like that."



